The paper deals with the problem of efficient nearest neighbor search, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves learning a routing function, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the method is evaluated through experiments, which is a common approach in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
